{"questionId":"33402080","questionHtml":"<p>Find the range of values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> for which a local minimum or maximum point exists.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>local min or max when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> has real solutions.<br>attempt to find the discriminant of numerator<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find the critical values of their quadratic equation or inequality<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>43649</mn><mo>…</mo></math></strong></em>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>436491</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>15</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><em><strong><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>15</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> is posititve)<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>44</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33402080","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.12b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the range of values of k for which a local minimum or maximum point exists.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}